The Chronicle Harare Bureau 
SIX men who burnt a Zupco bus and a car belonging to Chegutu East legislator Webster Shamu’s wife during the recent violent protests that rocked Harare and other cities have been jailed a combined 32 years. They were eight when they initially appeared in court but regional magistrate Mr Elijah Makomo acquitted two of them due to lack of evidence linking them to the offence. The ring leader Emmanuel Chari was sentenced to 7 years while five others were jailed 5 years each. More to follow…